1 A BILL for an Act to create and enact a new section to chapter 57-38 and a new subdivision to
2 subsection 7 of section 57-38-30.3 of the North Dakota Century Code, relating to a prison
3 industries workforce development income tax credit; to provide for a legislative management
4 study; and to provide an effective date.
5 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATIVE ASSEMBLY OF NORTH DAKOTA:
6 SECTION 1. A new section to chapter 57-38 of the North Dakota Century Code is created
7 and enacted as follows:
8 Prison industries workforce development credit.
9 1. A taxpayer that is a primary sector business, as defined in section 1 - 01 - 49, is allowed
10 a nonrefundable credit against the tax imposed under section 57 - 38 - 30 or 57 - 38 - 30.3
11 for the purchase of components of final manufactured products for which the taxpayer
12 subcontracted to use labor from prison industries for the purpose of workforce
13 development of inmates. The amount of the credit under this section is ten percent of
14 the cost incurred by the taxpayer in the taxable year for which the credit is claimed to
15 purchase the components. The credit must be claimed for the taxable year in which
16 the components are purchased.
17 2. The credit under this section may not exceed the taxpayer's liability as determined
18 under this chapter for any taxable year. If the amount of the credit determined under
19 this section exceeds the limitation under this subsection, the excess may be carried
20 forward to each of the next five succeeding taxable years.
21 3. The aggregate amount of credits allowed each calendar year under this section may
22 not exceed forty-five thousand dollars. If the aggregate amount of credits claimed
23 under this section:
